            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "When **-D** is used then the center of the wedge is at n * inc.  So in -A10 it is 0, 10, 20, .. including 270 (your -90).  So that one captures angles from 265 to 260 (-95 to -85).  It works as you say.\r\n\r\nFor the -A20 case it is the same, with bin centers at 0, 20, etc.  270 is not one of those, so it is 260 280 (or -100, -80).  Your point at -90 thus falls into the bin that is centered at -80 and goes from -90 to -70.\r\n\r\nSo in my thinking, both examples work.   I see no bug here.",
