            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Sorry, I didn't take the time to think about a clever solution.\n\nNow that I think about it, the \"expand/collapse code\" function could be really a good use to illustrate (MWE + figure) all options and parameters without overloading the already packed documentation. It would alleviate some misunderstanding like the current thread, or simply ease the learning curve.\n\nI understand it's more work, but maybe if the dev team comes up with a good framework, the community can tackle the basic examples (plot, grdimage, ...) while you focus on the more complex ones (greenspline, gravi, ...)\n\nThoughts (and prayers)?",
