        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Off today on trip to Cambridge so limited time, but some comments:\r\n\r\n1. I guess my comment above had to do with what I assumed was your confusion as to what **rose** does.  To me it is just like any other histogram I am aware of and hence the bins are fixed once you pick a width and offset.  You seemed surprised by what you got so I was wondering what lead you to believe it would not be a histogram.  If so, perhaps I could add a sentence or two to the docs to make it crystal clear.\r\n2. As for using the expand/collapse.  Yes, that is in general a good thing to show things.  However, it really only works well for very simple things.  Having very long scripts I think it a bit unwieldy.  As for the sample1d example, it shows all the various interpolators, so not sure if it is a great example of sample1d use, but I could be convinced.\r\n",
